The paper discusses a machine learning algorithm for tensor regression, which falls under the category of supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The algorithm also involves optimization techniques, such as projected gradient method and tensor power iterations, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions the use of randomized sketching, which is a technique commonly used in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses applications in spatio-temporal data, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
